    "state_reason": "completed",
    "title": "It is impossible to switch off binding for Tor",
    "body": "Bitcoin Core, by default, would bind to `127.0.0.1:8334` and treat incoming connections on that port as coming from the Tor network. It is not possible to disable that extra bind - only to change it to another address:port with the `-bind=...=onion` option.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\n\r\nIt must be possible to disable the extra bind if it is not needed.\r\n\r\nA workaround is to specify an address:port to which the bind fails, e.g. `-bind=1.1.1.1:1=onion`. The bind error is logged and ignored. Another workaround is to use `-listen=0`, but that prevents normal `-bind=...`.\r\n",
