      "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body": "If `-listenonion=0` disables the bind for onion, then this would brick any statically configured Tor services (in `torrc`).\r\n\r\nThe name `listenonion` is confusing IMO, because it instructs us to automatically create the Tor service via Tor control. We could still be listening on the Tor network if the service is configured in the Tor daemon itself (`torrc`) and in this case `listenonion=0`. Maybe `-autotorservice` is a better name...",
